        HELLO_AGAIN_THANK_YOU_FOR_HELPING_US_HM                              = 7017,  -- Hello again. Thank you for helping us. Hm? What am I still doing here?
        IT_S_A_FUNNY_STORY_REALLY_THE_PEOPLE                                 = 7018,  -- It's a funny story, really. The people who work here told me it's just not the same without me around.
        SO_I_VE_DECIDED_TO_STAND_HERE_AND                                    = 7019,  -- So I've decided to stand here and pray for the safety of all who make their living out on the sea.
        MAY_THE_SEA_BE_KIND_TO_THOSE_WHO                                     = 7020,  -- May the sea be kind to those who venture out in her realm...
        EH_WHAT_HAVE_WE_GOT_HERE_A_FLEDGLING                                 = 7021,  -- Eh? What have we got here? A fledgling adventurer! I have no business with the likes of you!
        I_M_NEREUS_THE_BEST_POTTER_HERE_IN                                   = 7022,  -- I'm Nereus, the best potter here in town! You must be a seasoned adventurer, are you not?
        WELL_UH_YES_I_AM_NO_NOT_REALLY                                       = 7023,  -- Well, uh... Yes, I am! No, not really.
        HEH_HEH_HEH_A_CONFIDENT_ONE_GOOD_GOOD                                = 7024,  -- Heh-heh-heh. A confident one! Good, good! You remind me of me when I was young!
        HEH_HEH_HEH_MODEST_ARE_WE_YOU_DON                                    = 7025,  -- Heh-heh-heh. Modest, are we? You don't have to be. I may be old, but I'm not blind.
        I_HAVE_A_TASK_THAT_I_CAN_ONLY                                        = 7026,  -- I have a task that I can only ask one such as you. Interested?
        INTERESTED_WHAT_IS_IT_I_M_TOO_BUSY                                   = 7027,  -- Interested? What is it? I'm too busy.
        I_M_GLAD_YOU_ASKED_YOU_SEE_I                                         = 7028,  -- I'm glad you asked. You see, I've been making pottery in this town for as long as I can remember... I'm what they'd call an artisan.
        I_VE_USED_CLAY_FROM_NEARBY_AREAS_IN                                  = 7029,  -- I've used clay from nearby areas in my work for many years, but I've been favoring clay from the Gusgen Mines lately.
        THE_THING_IS_THOUGH_A_BUNCH_OF_FIENDS                                = 7030,  -- The thing is, though, a bunch of fiends seem to have made those mines their home, and traders haven't been able to get any % out of there.
        IT_WASN_T_SO_HARD_TO_GET_SOME                                        = 7031,  -- It wasn't so hard to get some a few years back... You have to understand, to an artisan like myself, getting that clay is a matter of life and death.
        SO_I_NEED_A_STALWART_ADVENTURER_LIKE_YOU                             = 7032,  -- So...I need a stalwart adventurer like you to bring me %. I've heard you can find it deep within the mines.
        JUST_MAKE_SURE_TO_GET_A_MAP_SO                                       = 7033,  -- Just make sure to get a map so you don't get lost in there. Good luck!
        YOU_RE_TOO_BUSY_EH_WELL_THEN_COME                                    = 7034,  -- You're too busy, eh? Well, then...come back when you have time.
        YES_DID_YOU_FORGET_SOMETHING_PLEASE_GET_ME                           = 7035,  -- Yes? Did you forget something? Please get me % as soon as you can. Those mines are dangerous, though, so you take care, eh?
        OHO_WELL_DONE_A_GENUINE_AT_LAST_HERE                                 = 7036,  -- Oho! Well done! A genuine %, at last! Here's something for your troubles. Heh-heh.
        AH_YOU_VE_COME_BACK_I_NEED_ANOTHER                                   = 7037,  -- Ah, you've come back! I need another %. Can you go get some for me?
        VERY_GOOD_REMEMBER_IT_S_IN_THOSE_MINES                               = 7038,  -- Very good! Remember, it's in those mines I told you about before. Be careful, eh?
        THANKS_BUT_I_HAVE_ENOUGH_FOR_NOW_COME                                = 7039,  -- %? Thanks, but I have enough for now. Come back later. I may need some more then.
        EH_WHAT_DOES_AN_ADVENTURER_LIKE_YOU_WANT                             = 7040,  -- Eh? What does an adventurer like you want with me? Shouldn't you be out fighting beastmen, bringing peace to the world and all that?
        EH_ANOTHER_FLEDGLING_ADVENTURER_THERE_SEEM_TO_BE                     = 7041,  -- Eh? Another fledgling adventurer? There seem to be more and more of you people these days.
        I_MAY_BE_ABLE_TO_TEACH_YOU_A                                         = 7042,  -- I may be able to teach you a thing or two... Interested?
        I_M_GLAD_YOU_ARE_BUT_I_WON                                           = 7043,  -- I'm glad you are. But I won't talk for free. Why don't you bring me % for starters, eh?
        NOT_THAT_I_D_BE_TERRIBLY_UPSET_WITH                                  = 7044,  -- Not that I'd be terribly upset with %, provided you could get your hands on one.
        BRING_HER_WHAT_SHE_WANTS_SURE_MAYBE_LATER                            = 7045,  -- Bring her what she wants? Sure. Maybe later.
        GOOD_I_LL_BE_WAITING_HERE                                            = 7046,  -- Good. I'll be waiting here.
        OH_IT_S_FOR_YOUR_OWN_GOOD_YOU                                        = 7047,  -- Oh? It's for your own good, you know...
        OH_YOUR_LOSS_THEN_IT_S_SOMETHING_YOU                                 = 7048,  -- Oh? Your loss, then. It's something you really should know...
        WHERE_CAN_YOU_FIND_WELL_YOU_LL_JUST                                  = 7049,  -- Where can you find %? Well...you'll just have to look for yourself. Hoh-hoh.
        HOH_HOH_YES_THIS_IS_WHAT_I_ASKED                                     = 7050,  -- Hoh-hoh. Yes, this is what I asked for. I'm ready to talk now.
        SO_YOU_SEE_OH_DEAR_WHAT_WAS_I                                        = 7051,  -- So, you see... Oh, dear. What was I going to say? I forget so many things these days.
        HMM_YOU_KNOW_I_HEARD_IS_GOOD_FOR                                     = 7052,  -- Hmm...you know, I heard % is good for your memory.
        IF_YOU_BRING_ME_SOME_I_MIGHT_REMEMBER                                = 7053,  -- If you bring me some, I might remember what I was trying to tell you. Would you go look for some?
        THANK_YOU_I_LL_TRY_TO_REMEMBER_ON                                    = 7054,  -- Thank you. I'll try to remember on my own in the meantime.
        THAT_S_TOO_BAD_FOR_YOU_I_M                                           = 7055,  -- That's too bad for you. I'm sure whatever I was going to tell you would've helped you a lot. Are you sure you won't go?
        AH_YES_THIS_IS_IT_BUT_I_MANAGED                                      = 7056,  -- Ah! Yes, this is it. But I managed to remember without it. Hoh-hoh. Now, listen close...
        HAVE_YOU_EVER_SEEN_PEOPLE_USE_ABILITIES_FROM                         = 7057,  -- Have you ever seen people use abilities from jobs other than their main one? Those people are using something called support jobs.
        AND_IF_YOU_CAN_T_USE_SUPPORT_JOBS                                    = 7058,  -- And if you can't use support jobs, you don't deserve to be called an adventurer! But I can help you with that. Hoh-hoh.
        IT_S_ALL_UP_TO_YOU_BUT_IF                                            = 7059,  -- It's all up to you, but if you do want me to teach you...you'll have to bring me % first.
        HMM_I_SEE_YOU_VE_GOT_SOME_VIM                                        = 7060,  -- Hmm... I see you've got some vim after all. You may become a real adventurer yet. Hoh-hoh. All right, I'll teach you about support jobs as I promised.
        YOU_CAN_ADD_A_SUPPORT_JOB_TO_YOUR                                    = 7061,  -- You can add a support job to your main one wherever you can change jobs. Of course, it has to be a job you've already acquired.
        BUT_WHATEVER_YOU_CHOOSE_AS_YOUR_SUPPORT_JOB                          = 7062,  -- But whatever you choose as your support job, its effective level will never exceed half that of your main one. Your support job won't benefit from any experience points you gain, either. It is, after all, only meant to be supplemental.
        LET_ME_GIVE_YOU_AN_EXAMPLE_LET_S                                     = 7063,  -- Let me give you an example: Let's say you've achieved level 20 as a warrior and level 10 as a white mage. If you choose warrior as your main job and white mage as your support job, the following will occur...
        YOUR_WARRIOR_LEVEL_STAYS_THE_SAME_AT_20                              = 7064,  -- Your warrior level stays the same at 20, and your effective level in white mage also stays at 10--half the level of your main job. In this case, both jobs function to the fullest in their roles.
        NOW_SAY_YOU_CHOOSE_THE_SAME_WHITE_MAGE                               = 7065,  -- Now, say you choose the same white mage job as your main one and put your warrior job as your support job...
        YOUR_WHITE_MAGE_LEVEL_IS_STILL_10_BUT                                = 7066,  -- Your white mage level is still 10, but the effective level of your warrior job drops to 5, half the level of your main job. Now, that's a lot of wasted potential, isn't it? Hoh-hoh.
        AND_SELECTING_A_JOB_WITH_A_LEVEL_LESS                                = 7067,  -- And selecting a job with a level less than half of your main one as your support job isn't going to do you much good, either. Make sure you're using your jobs to their fullest when choosing support jobs.
        AS_TO_WHICH_JOB_IS_BEST_SUITED_TO                                    = 7068,  -- As to which job is best suited to your main job...ideally, it should be one that either covers your main job's weaknesses, or one that enhances its strengths.
        THAT_S_ABOUT_IT_IS_EVERYTHING_CLEAR                                  = 7069,  -- ...That's about it. Is everything clear?
        DO_YOU_UNDERSTAND_HOW_SUPPORT_JOBS_WORK_GOT                          = 7070,  -- Do you understand how support jobs work? Got it. Can you run that by me again?
        GOOD_THEN_WHY_ARE_YOU_STILL_HERE_GO                                  = 7071,  -- Good. Then why are you still here? Go try it out, already! And don't forget to thank me when it saves your skin. Hoh-hoh.
        OH_YOU_AGAIN_YOU_MUST_VE_THOUGHT_I                                   = 7072,  -- Oh, you again. You must've thought I was asking you to bring me those things out of greed. Hoh-hoh.
        BUT_YOU_REALIZE_I_WAS_ONLY_TESTING_YOU                               = 7073,  -- But you realize I was only testing you to see if you could actually get them. I used to be in the Market...Mooseket...Muskewhatchamacallits before, you know?
        YOU_LOOK_DUBIOUS_I_DID_TEACH_YOU_HOW                                 = 7074,  -- You look dubious. I did teach you how to use support jobs, didn't I? Well, you're free to believe whatever you want, but what you have now is real power. Use it wisely. Hoh-hoh.
        YOU_CAN_NOW_USE_SUPPORT_JOBS                                         = 7075,  -- You can now use support jobs!
        I_HEARD_ONCE_THAT_OLD_VERA_WAS_A                                     = 7076,  -- I heard once that old Vera was a warrior of some renown when she was young. It's before my time, of course, so I don't know if it is true.
        AND_BY_HER_AGE_I_D_SAY_ANYONE                                        = 7077,  -- And by her age, I'd say anyone who could testify to the veracity of that rumor would be long gone.
        FISHING_IS_AN_ART_I_HAVE_NOTHING_TO                                  = 7078,  -- Fishing is an art... I have nothing to say to one who has never held a fishing rod in his life.
        AH_I_SEE_YOU_HAVE_DABBLED_IN_THE                                     = 7079,  -- Ah, I see you have dabbled in the art of fishing...
        BUT_YOU_STILL_HAVE_A_LONG_WAY_TO                                     = 7080,  -- But you still have a long way to go. Come back when you've managed to catch some bigger game.
        TELL_ME_DO_YOU_REMEMBER_ALL_THE_CATCHES                              = 7081,  -- Tell me...do you remember all the catches you've made until now? Do you wish to know?
        DO_YOU_WANT_TO_KNOW_YOUR_FISHING_HISTORY                             = 7082,  -- Do you want to know your fishing history? Yes. No.
        OF_COURSE_YOU_DO_AS_WOULD_ALL_PRACTITIONERS                          = 7083,  -- Of course you do. As would all practitioners of the art.
        BUT_NO_ONE_CAN_KEEP_TRACK_OF_ALL                                     = 7084,  -- But no one can keep track of all their catches. Except for me. I can even tell you of your past achievements...for a price.
        I_ONLY_ASK_YOU_TO_BRING_ME_A                                         = 7085,  -- I only ask you to bring me %. A small price to pay for such information, isn't it?
        YOU_VE_BROUGHT_IT_VERY_WELL_I_WILL                                   = 7086,  -- You've brought it. Very well, I will tell you.
